data.name: Any%
data.rules:
Beat the game; no Cheat Engine.

Timing Starts upon clicking play.
Timing Ends at the final screen upon eating the 449ᵀᴴ fish.

data.name: Any% Good Ending
data.rules:
Timing starts when you press any key to wake the black cat. Timing finishes when the cat completely closes its eyes and the screen is black before the final cutscene.

The white cat must be picked up and the cutscene must be the good one.

data.name: Any% Bad Ending
data.rules: Timing starts when you press any key to wake the black cat. Timing finishes when the cat finishes closing its eyes and the screen is completely black before the final cutscene.

data.name: Any%
data.rules:
Timing starts upon first control of character and ends upon entering the final room to trigger the ending sequence.

For emulator runs, please state the name & version of the emulator used in your submission.

data.name: Any%
data.rules:
Any%:
- Collect all 24 EFFECTs and beat the game.
- Entering debug room is banned.

data.name: True Ending
data.rules:
True Ending:
- Complete the True Ending (known as: Rust Ending, Final Ending, or Ending-3).
 - Collect all 24 EFFECTs
 - Become Rust
 - Collect all 3 [        ] (Empty Boxes)
 - Kill Inner Demon
- Entering debug room is banned.

data.name: Glitchless
data.rules:
Any% Glitchless:
- Collect all 24 EFFECTs and beat the game.
- Using any glitches are banned.
 - Any kind of Speed Glitch
 - Open the menu where cannot be opened [e.g. Chair Menu, Instruction Glitch (Chair Storage)]
 - Sitting while Standing
 - Walk through Walls (Out of Bounds)

data.name: Bike Racing
data.rules:
Complete the Course by completing the objective of running over all of the King Chims.

Since All King Chims are required, the Bike Glitch is not allowed under this rule set.

This category is IGT and uses the Race Timer present on the screen at the end of the race for its final time.

Only submit IGT

data.name: Vol.3 All Fights
data.rules:
Must use a Vol.3 Redemption Save.
No other restrictions on savefile used.

You must complete all 16 avatar fights once.
Fights may be done in any order of the runner's choosing.

Timing Start
After removing all tutorial pop-ups from the fights, timing starts upon selecting the first fight.

Timing End
When the final data drain bullet lands in the 16th Avatar Fight.

data.rules:
In game time and Video evidence of entire run are required for submitting

Replays are not acceptable footage for submitting

data.name: Any%
data.rules: Beat the game on any mixture of difficulties (changing difficulty before each mission is fine) . Runs start from a fresh file. Time starts from selecting the first mission and ends when "Mission Complete" is shown after Bloch is defeated in Evil Summit. Runs are ranked by real time but we encourage you to submit a game time as well. Runs faster than 6th place played through emulators/running the game through a homebrew launcher will not be accepted due to load time advantages.

data.name: 00 Agent
data.rules: Beat the game on the 00 Agent difficulty in each level. Runs start from a fresh file. Time starts from selecting the first mission and ends when "Mission Complete" is shown after Bloch is defeated in Evil Summit. Runs are ranked by real time but we encourage you to submit a game time as well. Runs faster than 6th place played through emulators/running the game through a homebrew launcher will not be accepted due to load time advantages.

data.name: Operative
data.rules: Emulators are fine. Pausing at any time (aside from at the end of Dangerous Pursuit in order to reach the results screen quicker) is not allowed.  Runs must be done in a single segment. Reloading checkpoints by death or other means is not allowed. First place requires a video to be accepted, all lower placements require at least a picture of the IGT shown on the results screen.

data.name: 00 Agent
data.rules: Emulators are fine. Pausing at any time (aside from at the end of Dangerous Pursuit in order to reach the results screen quicker) is not allowed.  Runs must be done in a single segment. Reloading checkpoints by death or other means is not allowed. First place requires a video to be accepted, all lower placements require at least a picture of the IGT shown on the results screen.

data.name: All Tokens
data.rules: Collect all of the golden 007 tokens found in each level on any mixture of difficulties (changing difficulty before each mission is fine). Runs start from a file in which each level has been beaten with a gold or platinum rank. Levels must be played in correct order. Time starts from selecting the first mission and ends when "Mission Complete" is shown after Bloch is defeated in Evil Summit. Runs are ranked by real time but we encourage you to submit a game time as well. Runs faster than 6th place played through emulators/running the game through a homebrew launcher will not be accepted due to load time advantages.
